President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Charles Blahous as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Social Security Trust Funds. Blahous is currently a Senior Fellow at the Hudson Institute, specializing in domestic economic policy. He has previously served in various roles related to retirement security and economic policy, including as Deputy Director of President Bush's National Economic Council and as the Executive Director of the bipartisan President's Commission to Strengthen Social Security. Blahous has a Ph.D. in computational quantum chemistry and an A.B. from Princeton University.